summary: Y'all so I just need to let you know about these makeup brushes I found. So I have a problem with makeup and I have to buy...
body:
Y'all so I just need to let you know about these makeup brushes I found.

So I have a problem with makeup and I have to buy everything cute, especially the brushes. You can never have to much right?

Well my Amazon is basically a recommendation of all things make up. The other day I had this set of brushes pop up for $16 and I thought the design looked really familiar.

While it’s not labeled Captain Marvel it is the design she has on her chest, and I was kind of surprised how quickly people have a full set already up. It used to be hard to find merch with her logo on it. I got really excited but then also skeptical. It was a 12 set of brushes for $16, which sometimes its probably not the greatest quailty but I went ahead and ordered a set because it’s on 16 and why not. I’m an adult who pays her taxes. I do what I want!

They came in today and y'all I’m so excited. The box was a little beaten from shipping but I thought the packaging was cute, and as long as the actual product is fine I don’t care if the box is a little damaged. I throw them away anyways.

I did not expect the quality to be so nice. The brushes themselves are so incredibly soft and they actually have some weight to them(not like a hollow weight some of the cheaper brands out there). I’ve already been messing with to see if any of the bristles fall out and so far they’re all intact. But more importantly; look how pretty they are!

I haven’t used them yet(obviously) but Im excited to try out tomorrow. I’m also really excited because I’ve been looking for a highlighter brush forever like the second one on the left in forever and now I finally have one!

I just had to gush because I didn’t expect them to be so nice.

title: Captain Marvel CONTROVERSY
body:
People thought Black Panther would be a bust and look how that turned out. More money made in the US than in any other country COMBINED. 

Now we’re back with the political agenda surrounding Captain Marvel, who… isn’t smiling enough?! Okay, this is a stupid joke. Of course she’ll be smiling more in the movie. The trailer is just that: a trailer. A preview of things to come.

Furthermore, she’s a soldier in the military. Not a lot of time to just smile and chit-chat. If we’re gonna put logic into play, let’s not demonize a woman in the military for taking her job seriously. I know Captain Marvel’s been rumored to be snarky and even funny, but we got enough of that out of Black Widow in the Avengers’ films. Having a woman in a serious role for Marvel might be a good change. Hell, I’m sure this film will be a success whether or not it’s furthering some political agenda. 

Speaking of which… why was Wonder Woman left out of the conversation then? Oh right, that’s a DC film. Seriously, if Captain Marvel can get a scene that gets me as excited as Wonder Woman did despite its cheesiness, I’ll say it’s well worth a watch. 

I’m excited for Brie Larson. I’m excited for Captain Marvel’s entrance into the MCU. And I’m excited for the smug jerks who think women should just sit still and look pretty to shut up when she hits the scene.
